            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@justinmk yeah, probably a good idea.\r\n\r\nFor now I extracted in just into a local function, not to lsp util as you mentioned in the issue, pretty much because:\r\n- it's not a reusable debounce as was initially discussed, but a specific behavior;\r\n- this behavior is needed only for diagnostic at the moment and it's used only 2 times in identical cases so I'm not sure what a good interface would be outside these use cases, if extracted out of the module.\r\n\r\nPotential uses cases are: current line blame, current line code action tooltip.\r\nThey aren't part of the core library and neither they are planned afaik.\r\n\r\nSo let me know what you think.",
